note: Pittsburgh will be a top-10 option for Week 6 against Geno Smith - a QB who hasn't started in four seasons. Expectations should be tempered, however, as this Steelers' squad has underachieved on the defensive side of the ball this season.

Buffalo's D/ST has been the top-scoring defense for two weeks straight and three weeks in total this season. Don't expect that to change in Week 6 against a Titans' offense surrendering the eight-most points to opposing D/ST's.
New England's offense has been pedestrian this season, and opposing D/ST's have scored the fifth-most fantasy points this season. Dallas is a clear top-3 play in Week 6.
This Cardinal defense has been much better than advertised, finishing as the DST1 twice and a top-12 option three times on the year. Expect favorable results once again in Week 6.
There's no reason to start a Patriots' defense that couldn't stop Houston and had its best games against the Dolphins and Jets. The matchup with Dallas is one to avoid.
